    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3877" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐτεός</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">true,
            real;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νεικεῖν πόλλ᾽ ἐτεά τε καὶ οὐχί</span>,
          ‘reproaches true and untrue,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
            20.255</span></i>; elsewhere only <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐτεόν</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">the truth</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">truly;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἰ δή ῥ̓ ἐτεόν γε καὶ ἀτρεκέως
            ἀγορεύεις</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.53</span></i>, and
          freq. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἰ ἐτεόν γε</span> (sc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐστί</span>), <i><span class="en">Il.
            14.125</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
          3.122</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
